Set preferences
==
# git config —global user.name Phincy
# git config —global user.email phincy.l@flipkart.com
# git config —global core.editor vi
# git config —list

# git help config

Get preferences
==

# git config user.name
# git config core.editor


These settings are saved in the ~/.gitconfig file


Initialise new git repo
==
# mkdir /path/to/repo 
# cd  /path/to/repo
# git init

clone a repo
===
git clone git@githum.com/path/tp/git

git add *

git commit -a -m “adding"

git push

git status

git rm file

git rm —cached
git log

git log -p




=============




